jeremyText="Attacking these from the front does not work very well, and unless their front armor is not open, even a shot to the back won't work for you very well. When it does open up its front armor, it will put up an energy shield and fire a quick laser at you." chaoText="Seems these shielding type bots are becoming a lot more common. At least these don't absorb energy with their shield." devText="When coding this enemy, I realized attacking from the front/back of enemies was going to be a more common thing in DT3. This prompted me to create a sub-class to taking damage for enemy objects that handled attacks coming from different directions based on the enemy's facing."
